Who's It For?

Anyone using the Saxon Algebra 1/2 Homeschool textbook should consider this companion course. You will learn the material faster, retain it longer and earn a better grade.

How It Works

  • Identify the chapter in your Saxon Algebra 1/2 Homeschool textbook with which you need help.
  • Find the corresponding chapter within our Saxon Algebra 1/2 Homeschool Textbook Companion Course.
  • Watch fun videos that cover the algebra topics you need to learn or review.
  • Complete the quizzes to test your understanding.
  • If you need additional help, re-watch the videos until you've mastered the material or submit a question for one of our instructors.

Why It Works

  • Fun Content: These videos make learning Saxon Algebra 1/2 Homeschool fun with engaging animation and real-world examples.
  • Great Instructors: Study.com uses exceptional educators who can take concepts like solving equations and make them easy to understand.
  • Multiple Ways to Learn: Watch videos or read the lesson transcript.
  • Easy to Use: Access this textbook companion on any smartphone, tablet or laptop.

Course Topics

Students will be able to learn all the algebra topics in the textbook with this engaging course, including:

  • Whole numbers
  • Fractions, decimals and Roman numerals
  • Graphs, charts and graphing
  • Sets, real numbers and number theory
  • Measurement and conversions
  • Ratios, proportion and percents
  • Roots and exponents
  • Statistics and probability
  • Expressions, equations and polynomials
  • Functions and introduction to trigonometry
  • Lines, planes, and figures
  • Circumference, perimeter, area and volume
  • Constructing figures
  • Pythagorean Theorem
